The paper deals with physical-layer security in a cognitive radio system, which involves wireless communication, network security, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which focuses on the fundamental limits of data communication and storage. The paper also discusses the coordination and scheduling of multiple users, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The analysis of diversity order and outage probability is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
